Option to play left channel (channel 0)  in both speakers:
-af channels=2:2:0:1:0:0

To play right channel (channel 1) in both speakers:
-af channels=2:2:1:0:1:1

Use '-ac' and '-vc' to use audio and video codec. For example, to play a file
named dvdrip.xvid.dts.3cd-waf_01.avi, we may use this command:
mplayer -ac dts *.avi

